// @check
// @error float literal overflows f64
// @error float literal overflows f64
// A float literal whose magnitude rounds past the largest finite double names
// a value f64 cannot represent — and VL has no infinity spelling to write the
// result honestly, so it is a compile error (silent ±inf would be a lossy
// implicit conversion; runtime arithmetic still yields ±inf per IEEE-754).
// The judgement is the byte encoder's own rounding, so it is exact at the
// boundary: the max-finite literal below is fine, the next tick past the
// overflow midpoint rejects, sign included.
print(.0)
print(-.0)
print(.0 > 0.0) // the largest finite double still compiles clean
